File: Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu. JOHANNESBURG - Tributes have poured in for outgoing Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu. Makwetu died in hospital aged 54. The Auditor-General's office released a statement confirming that he was diagnosed with Stage 4 lung cancer in 2018. READ: Outgoing Auditor-General Kimi Makwetu dies aged 54 During his address on Wednesday, President Cyril Ramaphosa paid tribute to Makwetu. "During his time as auditor-general, Mr Makwetu served this country with dedication, distinction, and with great integrity. "Our thoughts and prayers are with his family at this time of great sorrow," he said. Chairperson of the Standing Committee on the Auditor-General, Sakhumzi Somyo, described Makwetu as a professional man. Outgoing Auditor-General, Kimi Makwetu has died in hospital aged 54. The auditor general's office has released a statement confirming that he was diagnosed with stage 4 lung cancer in 2018. For more, Clement Manyathela and Sally Burdett spoke to the Chairperson of the Standing Committee on the Auditor-General Sakhumzi Somyo. Courtesy #DStv403 Scopa chairperson Mkhuleko Hlengwa says Makwetu led from the front with integrity. Outgoing Auditor General Kimi Makwethu has died. He was diagnosed with stage 4 lung cancer just two years ago. Courtesy #DStv403